1. 飲茶  
廣東話：我阿媽成日話「去飲茶啦」，即刻拖我去元朗點心街。  
English: My mom always says "Let's go yum cha," then she drags me to Yuen Long dim sum street.

2. 圖書館  
廣東話：我個仔成日喺圖書館溫書，返到屋企就瞓覺。  
English: My son always studies at the library and falls asleep as soon as he gets home.

3. 養聲  
廣東話：歌手開演唱會前一定要養聲，唔可以食辣嘢。  
English: Singers must rest their voice before concerts and can't eat spicy food.

4. 票尾  
廣東話：記得留返張票尾，萬一有問題可以攞返去換。  
English: Remember to keep the ticket stub in case there's a problem and you need to exchange it.

5. hacker  
廣東話：嗰個hacker入侵咗公司個系統，偷咗好多客戶資料。  
English: That hacker broke into the company's system and stole a lot of customer data.

6. 石斛蘭  
廣東話：我阿嫲最鍾意養石斛蘭，成個露台都係。  
English: My grandma loves growing dendrobium orchids, the whole balcony is full of them.

7. 吊詭  
廣東話：呢件事真係吊詭，明明係假嘅，但係又好似真嘅。  
English: This matter is really paradoxical, it's clearly fake but somehow seems real.

8. 吊詭  
廣東話：佢講嘅說話好吊詭，聽落去唔合理但又好似有道理。  
English: What he said is very paradoxical, it sounds unreasonable but also seems to make sense.

9. 各為其主  
廣東話：兩兄弟喺商場上各為其主，最後變成對頭人。  
English: The two brothers served different masters in business and eventually became enemies.

10. 軨蓋  
廣東話：架車個軨蓋跌咗，要即刻去整返好。  
English: The car's hubcap fell off, need to get it fixed immediately.

11. 打哥夫  
廣東話：我老細每個禮拜日都約人去打哥夫。  
English: My boss goes golfing every Sunday with people.

12. 免揀  
廣東話：呢檔生果檔寫住「免揀」，你唔好逐個逐個摸啦。  
English: This fruit stall has a "no picking" sign, don't touch each one individually.

13. 擺闊佬  
廣東話：佢中咗六合彩之後成日擺闊佬，請晒全公司食飯。  
English: After winning the lottery, he's always showing off his wealth, treating the whole company to meals.

14. 廣播劇  
廣東話：我阿嫲以前好鍾意聽收音機嘅廣播劇。  
English: My grandma used to love listening to radio dramas.

15. 錄影機  
廣東話：我哋用部錄影機拍低個婚禮，留返做紀念。  
English: We used the video recorder to film the wedding as a keepsake.

16. 吟詩吟唔甩  
廣東話：閉路電視影到你偷嘢，真係吟詩吟唔甩啦！  
English: The CCTV caught you stealing, there's no way you can deny it!

17. 佈道大會  
廣東話：教會下個月會搞個佈道大會，歡迎所有人參加。  
English: The church is holding an evangelistic rally next month, everyone is welcome to attend.

18. 寫手  
廣東話：佢係個自由寫手，專門幫雜誌寫稿。  
English: He's a freelance writer who writes articles for magazines.

19. 寫手  
廣東話：有啲學生請寫手代做功課，呢種行為好唔應該。  
English: Some students hire ghostwriters to do their homework, this behavior is very inappropriate.

20. 代打  
廣東話：佢請人代打升級，結果畀遊戲公司封咗帳號。  
English: He hired someone to level up his account, and ended up getting banned by the game company.

21. 茶碗  
廣東話：我喺日本買咗個好靚嘅茶碗返嚟。  
English: I bought a beautiful tea bowl from Japan.

22. 茶隔  
廣東話：用茶隔隔住啲茶葉，咁就唔會飲到一啖茶葉。  
English: Use a tea strainer to filter the tea leaves so you don't drink any leaves.

23. 只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈  
廣東話：老闆自己成日遲到，但係員工遲一分鐘就鬧，真係只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈。  
English: The boss is always late but scolds employees for being one minute late, truly a case of "rules for thee but not for me."

24. 獨唱  
廣東話：佢喺音樂會度獨唱咗首《月亮代表我的心》。  
English: She performed a solo of "The Moon Represents My Heart" at the concert.

25. 快人快事  
廣東話：佢做嘢快人快事，一個鐘就搞掂晒。  
English: He works efficiently and finishes everything in one hour.

26. 四腳獸  
廣東話：商場保安發現廁所有四腳獸，即刻報警。  
English: Mall security discovered people being intimate in the toilet and immediately called the police.

27. 無米粥  
廣東話：我哋先煲吓無米粥，睇吓大家有冇興趣先再詳細傾。  
English: Let's have a preliminary discussion first to see if everyone's interested before going into details.

28. 義會  
廣東話：以前啲街坊會搞義會互相幫助，而家都冇乜人搞喇。  
English: In the past, neighbors would organize mutual aid societies, but now hardly anyone does it anymore.

29. 榜文  
廣東話：學校貼咗張榜文出嚟，公佈考試成績。  
English: The school posted an announcement listing the exam results.

30. MK名  
廣東話：佢個Facebook用咗個MK名，叫「絕對↘愛♥你」。  
English: His Facebook uses an MK-style name, "Absolutely↘Love♥You." [end of text]


